This example uses images and texture fills to provide a 3D beveled border effect for the panels in this view.
The corner cells have images (7x7 pixels) that render the corners of the border.
The top, bottom, and sides use a texture (7x3 pixels).
To see the settings for this effect, select the the Cell Constraints panel in the designer. Then select a corner or top, bottom, or side cell. Press the Fill button to examine the fill properties for the cell.
